craterdog.collections.primitives

Class HashTable<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • craterdog.collections.primitives.HashTable<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of keys in the table.
    V - The type of values in the table.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<K,V>

    public final class HashTable<K,V>
extends java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
implements java.util.Map<K,V>, java.lang.Cloneable
    This class provides an implementation of hash table that scales up and down geometrically as the number of elements increases and decreases. When the number of elements in the table reaches its current capacity, it automatically doubles its capacity. When the number of elements drops below 1/4th of its current capacity, it automatically halves its capacity. This ensures a hysteresis of 1/2 its capacity so that it won't oscillate up and down with small changes in number of elements near a boundary condition.
    Author:
    Derk Norton
